# Entity & DAO Best Practices (MeApp Android)

## 1. Entity Definition
- Define all Room entities in `data/storage/db/entity/`.
- Annotate with `@Entity`, specify table name, and use `@PrimaryKey`.
- Use `@ForeignKey` and `@Relation` for relationships.
- All properties must be documented with KDoc.
- Use data classes for entities.

## 2. DAO Definition
- Define all DAOs in `data/storage/db/dao/`.
- Annotate with `@Dao`.
- Use `@Insert`, `@Update`, `@Delete`, and `@Query` for CRUD operations.
- Return `suspend` or `Flow<T>` for async operations.
- All methods must be documented with KDoc.

## 3. Relationships
- Use `@Embedded` and `@Relation` for one-to-one and one-to-many relationships.
- Document the relationship in the entity and DAO.

---

**Example:**

```kotlin
// data/storage/db/entity/ExampleEntity.kt
/**
 * Entity class representing the example table.
 */
@Entity(tableName = "example")
data class ExampleEntity(
    @PrimaryKey val id: String,
    val name: String
)

// data/storage/db/dao/ExampleDao.kt
/**
 * DAO for example operations.
 */
@Dao
interface ExampleDao {
    /**
     * Insert an example entity.
     */
    @Insert(onConflict = OnConflictStrategy.REPLACE)
    suspend fun insert(example: ExampleEntity)

    /**
     * Get all examples.
     */
    @Query("SELECT * FROM example")
    fun getAll(): Flow<List<ExampleEntity>>
}
```
